result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamie John Zellner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Substantial Battery-Intend Bodily Harm [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(2).
  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Eamon Collins Guerin in court, defendant Jamie John Zellner not in court, in custody.  Michael Davis Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded. Court reviewed Sentencing Memorandum. Statements by parties and defendant. 

AS TO COUNT 3
The court sentenced the defendant to 70 DAYS in the House of Correction, with credit for 70 DAYS time served, CONCURRENT (credit to apply to Count 1 as well) this is a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION. Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including DNA & DV Surcharge from 25% of prison funds on counts 1 & 2, balance to be collected by DOC on extended supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment. Court WAIVED all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. 

AS TO COUNT 1
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 2 YEARS, consecutive, credit for 172 DAYS time served, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 1 YEAR, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

AS TO COUNT 2
The court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM term in the Wisconsin State Prison of 4 YEARS & 6 MONTHS, consecutive, the term of INITIAL CONFINEMENT is 1 YEAR & 6 MONTHS, the term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
-Complete a Batterer's Intervention Program.
-Mental health evaluation, take all prescribed medications.
-AODA assessment, comply with recommended treatment.
-Absolute sobriety, random urine screens.
-Treatment and/or counseling as determined by agent.
-No contact with firearms.
-No contact with victim.
-Provide DNA Sample.
-No driving without a valid license.
-Obtain/maintain employment.
-No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause.
-Obtain GED/HSED.
-Pay all mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges including DNA & DV Surcharge from 25% of prison funds, balance to be collected by DOC on extended supervision, failure to pay results in a civil judgment.
-Court WAIVED all NON-Mandatory court costs, fees, and surcharges. 

*Court finds defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program OR the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.
*Court advised defendant of right to seek post conviction relief.
*Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER.
*Court advised due to DV conviction under federal law the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession.
*Court advised due to felony conviction the defendant is prohibited from firearm possession, and defendant's voting rights are suspended and may not vote until civil rights are restored.
